      "content": "\"Observe the difference, men; it is etched not just in their customs, but in the very sinew and spirit of their people. They possess a raw, untamed vitality, yes, but it is a vitality without direction, a brute force lacking the refinement of intellect. We, by nature, are built for governance, for the delicate application of law and reason. It is not merely a choice, but a fundamental truth of nature that the superior mind must guide the less developed, lest chaos consume all.\"",
